Sociological Forum is a quarterly peer-reviewed academic journal published by Wiley-Blackwell on behalf of the Eastern Sociological Society. It has been published since 1986. The current editor is Karen A. Cerulo (Rutgers University). The journal covers all areas of sociology and related fields, emphasizing innovative direction in sociological research.
According to the Journal Citation Reports, the journal has a 2011 impact factor of 0.908, ranking it 58th out of 137 journals in the category "Sociology".


